On September 22, 2023, the President signed a new law called H.R. 2544, also known as the "Securing the U.S. Organ Procurement and Transplantation Network Act." This law enables the awarding of multiple grants, contracts, or cooperative agreements to operate the Organ Procurement and Transplantation Network. The President expressed gratitude to Representatives Bucshon and Kelly, as well as Senators Wyden, Grassley, Cardin, Young, and Cassidy for their leadership in the development of this legislation.